https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JwPYjnhah3g

Download and install IntelliJ IDEA opensource tool for Java Debug.

Open Interlli JDEA and click Create new Project

select Gradle. 

select Project SDK.
1.8(java version "1.8.0_222"

Select Additional Libraries and Frameworks
Java

Click next

Groupid: org.mixwell
Artifactid: java-gradle-ij-example

Click finish.
IJ will create sample gradle project at sleected (created) folder. 
C:\Workarea\test\java-gradle-ij-example
build.gradle config file is exist.

At the top message bar "You can configure Gradle wrapper to use distribution with sources. It will provide IDE with Gradle API/DSL document... OK, apply suggestion!

At the right bar it has gradle item to run tasks such as build.

at JAVA-IDE project view select src,  add JAVA class file Main.Class


public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println(args[0]);
        System.out.println("Hellow JAVA from amin!");
    }

}

run from Run meun.
Also could set run Eidt Configuration of Run Main => Program Agrument: "intellJ IDEA says Hello!"

